, but it remains serious and substantive. The book serves as an excellent and comprehensive introduction to Marion’s thought and work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPhilosopherszFrancevInterviews. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aReligion. 4aTheology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh  aJean-Luc Marion.  aRene Descartes.  aevent.  agift.  ametaphysics.  aphenomenology.  arevelation.  asaturated phenomenon.1 aArbib, Dan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGschwandtner, Christina M.1 aTracy, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTracy, David.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823275786zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823275786423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823275786/original  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK